					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">FLEX6000 FGPAs are $25-$35, looking on digikey.  They have about that many I/Os, on a 144-pin TQFP.  I've been looking at some MAX7000 CPLDs also.
<br />
<br />119 I/Os sounds like a lot, how'd you get that figure?  I know you can at least connect the PRG data bus all together, and I doubt the mapper logic would need to know every single address line (but I dunno what your design has in mind, heheh).
<br />
<br />With memory cards I think it would depend on what's in the particular SD card used, it's probably safe to say you'll need a 5V/3V transceiver.  But at least it's not many lines.</div>

